cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of identifying synaptic partners in electron microscopy images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a convolutional network for training, which suggests the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques, which could fall under the category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
